# Winkart Backend API Walkthrough

We have successfully built and verified the complete, production-ready Django backend API for **WINKART** integrated with MongoDB. The system satisfies every requirement from the specification doc and matches the in-store "check-before-buy" workflow.

---

## 1. System Architecture

The project has been structured cleanly into modular sub-applications under the [winkart_backend](file:///d:/PythonPrograms/Winkart/winkart_backend) directory:

- **MongoDB Config ([database.py](file:///d:/PythonPrograms/Winkart/winkart_backend/winkart_backend/database.py))**: Connection client to the local MongoDB server (`mongodb://localhost:27017`) and initialization code to configure optimal indexes (unique email/phone, geospatial `2dsphere` indexes on shop locations, and text index on product catalogs).
- **Authentication App ([authentication/](file:///d:/PythonPrograms/Winkart/winkart_backend/authentication))**: Custom stateless JWT authentication (`pyjwt` and DRF custom backend) for users stored in MongoDB, handling Customer and Seller profiles, shop settings, business hours, and file uploads.
- **Core Catalog App ([core/](file:///d:/PythonPrograms/Winkart/winkart_backend/core))**: Management of Level 1 and Level 2 Categories, Geospatial shop location search (`$near` queries), Product details and attributes, and scheduled active banner/video promotions.
- **Operations App ([operations/](file:///d:/PythonPrograms/Winkart/winkart_backend/operations))**: Customer shopping carts, Checkout to generate digital **Bills/Invoices**, dynamic invoice PDF downloads using `reportlab`, and bulk Excel exports/imports using `pandas` and `openpyxl`.
- **Marketing App ([marketing/](file:///d:/PythonPrograms/Winkart/winkart_backend/marketing))**: Mappings and recommendations for Upselling (higher-end items) and Cross-selling (complementary items) configurations.

